<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05118</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE COLLECTION OR SOLICITATION OF USAGE FEES FOR TOILETS IN BOTH PUBLIC AND COMMERCIAL PLACES, APPROPRIATING FUNDS AND PROVIDING MECHANISMS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Free Toilet Use Act Of 2017</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Criminalizes the practice of charging of fees for the use of toilets in order to give access to the public especially the underprivileged and the marginalized.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>LACSON, VIRGILIO S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-02-22</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (080 2017-03-08)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2017-02-28</td></tr></table>